text.section:
Except where a term of natural life without the possibility of parole is imposed, a sentence for the following persons shall include a term of lifetime sexual offender supervision:
a person who is a sexually violent predator;
a person who has been convicted of a violation of § 3-303, § 3-304, § 3-305, or § 3-306(a)(1) or (2) of the Criminal Law Article;
a person who has been convicted of a violation of § 3-309, § 3-310, or § 3-311 of the Criminal Law Article or an attempt to commit a violation of § 3-306(a)(1) or (2) of the Criminal Law Article;
a person who has been convicted of a violation of § 3-602 of the Criminal Law Article involving a child under the age of 12 years;
a person who is required to register under § 11-704(c) of this subtitle; and
a person who has been convicted more than once arising out of separate incidents of a crime that requires registration under this subtitle.

section.section:
The conditions of lifetime sexual offender supervision may include:
monitoring through global positioning satellite tracking or equivalent technology;
where appropriate and feasible, restricting a person from living in proximity to or loitering near schools, family child care homes, child care centers, and other places used primarily by minors;
restricting a person from obtaining employment or from participating in an activity that would bring the person into contact with minors;
requiring a person to participate in a sexual offender treatment program;
prohibiting a person from using illicit drugs or alcohol;
authorizing a parole and probation agent to access the person's personal computer to check for material relating to sexual relations with minors;
requiring a person to take regular polygraph examinations;
prohibiting a person from contacting specific individuals or categories of individuals; and
any other conditions deemed appropriate by the sentencing court or juvenile court.
